Comments:	Tin is a full-screen easy to use Usenet newsreader for
		the terminal. It can read news locally (eg. var/spool/news)
		or remotely ("rtin" or "tin -r" option) via an NNTP (Network
		News Transport Protocol, RFC3977) or NNTPS (RFC8143) server.

		Example tin.defaults file is at:
		/usr/local/etc/tin/tin.defaults
		Copy to /etc/tin/tin.defaults and customise if desired. For
		posting from a system without a Fully Qualified Domain Name,
		you need "disable_sender=ON".

